(273, '1234400578', 'Cocoa', '1234400578.jpg', 'Cocoa - The seed of this South American tree (Theobroma Cacao) have been used for food since ancient times, the Aztecs of Central America called it food for the gods, believing it was of devine origin. This is also reflected in its scientific name, Theos = gods, broma = food. In Aztec community only those of importance were allowed to drink the bitter beverage made form pounded roasted cacao beans, maize and chilli pepper. Today major cocoa producers include Brazil, Ghana and Ivory Coast ', NULL, 355, '2009-02-12 00:44:34', '2009-02-12 00:44:34', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(274, '1234400712', 'Shea Butter', '1234400712.jpg', 'Shea butter tree - origin: Guinea Savannah of Africa. It is called after Mungo Park. The fruit-pulp is sweet and commonly eaten unprocessed by both humans and animals. the kernels are rich in oil (45 - 55%) by weight) known as shea butter which is extracted after pounding and grinding into paste the roasted kernels. The shea butter is used extensively as vegetable oil in cooking, soap and candle making and in cosmetics.', NULL, 423, '2009-02-12 00:44:34', '2009-02-12 00:44:34', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
