(346, '1236296735', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Paga Crocodile pond', '1236296735.jpg', 'Paga is noted for it''s sacred pond, which is a sanctuary for crocodiles. The crocodiles are said to be totems for the people of Kassena, who reside in Paga and the surrounding communities.', NULL, 5710, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(347, '1236296992', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Ada Foah', '1236296992.jpg', 'Accra Tema Yacht Club (ATYC) is loacted in Ada, at the mouth of the River Volta, some 112km by road from Accra. However, most of their members live in Accra and there is an active social scene revolving around Ryans Irish Pub, Osu, which is now their Accra Home', NULL, 2081, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(348, '1236321188', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Dodi Princess', '1236321188.JPG', 'Journey on the Volta Lake from Akosombo Harbour to Dodi Island.6 hours on the boat There is a nice high live band. You can dance, eat drink, tan the whole day, or watch the river sides. ', NULL, 1505, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(349, '1236321505', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Kakum National Park', '1236321505.jpg', 'Kakum National Park is in the southern part of Ghana, it is the best preserved region of virgin rainforest in the country and provides the easiest access to the rainforest for tourists along with the famous canopy walkway. The easiest starting point for a trip to Kakum is Cape Coast, the regional capital. Tro-tro''s run regularly to Kakum and beyond, alternatively you can charter a taxi.the park is approximately a 1 hour journey from Cape Coast.', NULL, 1561, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(350, '1236322170', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Proverbial Coffins in Accra', '1236322170.jpg', 'In Ghana, carving of coffins in various styles started in 1977,when a carpenter named Ataa Owuo lost his Grandmother and carved a coffin in the shape of an aeroplane. ', NULL, 2738, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(351, '1236322910', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Nzulezu', '1236322910.jpg', 'The famous village on stilts is located 90km west of Takoradi about an hour''s drive from the beautiful beaches of Busua.', NULL, 5308, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(352, '1236323265', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Cape Coast Castle', '1236323265.jpg', 'Cape Coast grew around Cape Coast Castle, now a World Heritage Site. It was converted to a castle by the Dutch in 1637, then expanded by the Swedes in 1652 and captured by the British in 1664.It is situated 165 km west of Accra on the Gulf of Guinea.', NULL, 2849, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(353, '1236323499', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Elmina Castle', '1236323499.jpg', 'Elmina Castle was erected by the Portuguese in 1482.It was the first trading post built on the Gulf of Guinea, so is the oldest European building in existence below the Sahara.It is situated 165 km west of Accra on the Gulf of Guinea.', NULL, 1227, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(354, '1236323645', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Fort Prinzenstein', '1236323645.jpg', 'This Fort was among the four major Danish structures in Ghana, built in the commercial capital of the 36 Anlo towns, Keta in 1784 AD.', NULL, 1722, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 1, 1, 1, NULL),
(355, '1236324606', 'Tourist sites in Ghana : Paragliding', '1236324606.jpg', 'The Paragliding Festival is held in March or April of 2008. This festival is hosted by the Ghanaian Ministry of Tourism at Kwahu in the Eastern region', NULL, 1516, '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '2009-03-05 23:33:09', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 4, 1, 1, NULL),
