(647, '1240179381', 'Tetteh Quarshie''s Cocoa Farm', '1240179381.jpg', 'This was the first cocoa farm established in the country. The cocoa seeds are believed to have been brought from Fernando Po Island by Tetteh Quarshie, who set up the farm at Mampong-Akwapim in 1879. The farm was replanted in 1960, but 3 of the original trees still remain to this day. ', NULL, 655, '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(648, '1240179659', 'The First Cocoa Tree', '1240179659.jpg', 'One of the 3 remaining original trees in the farm.', 'r0msHqxQ-c0', 401, '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(649, '1240180020', 'Cocoa Pod', '1240180020.jpg', 'It''s not true that Tetteh Quarshie swallowed some cocoa seeds in a way of smuggling it. He actually hid 11 cocoa pods in his tools box and smuggled it to Ghana, 5 of which didn''t do well at his hometown Teshie, because of weather conditions so he relocated to Mampong where he had his first farm in 1879.', 'ys0wd5IRPlk', 817, '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 4, 1, 1, NULL),
(650, '1240180519', 'Tetteh Quarshie''s Sandals', '1240180519.jpg', 'Slipper of a type used by Tetteh Quarshie. From this simple beginning, Ghana was destined to become the world''s largest supplier of cocoa beans from 1910 until 1980. This Farm is at Mampong, less than an hour''s drive from Accra.', 'r0msHqxQ-c0', 729, '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 8, 2, 1, NULL),
(651, '1240186357', 'Tetteh Quarshie Cocoa Farm', '1240186357.jpg', 'Pioneer of Ghana Cocoa Industry. Born 1842 parents of Ga origin was a blacksmith by\r\nProfession visited Fernandopo in 1870. Brought cocoa pods on his return in 1876.Raised a farm At Mampong-Akwapim after three years efforts in 1879 died on 22nd  dec 1892. He was 50years.\r\n', NULL, 1154, '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '2009-04-19 21:03:55', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
(652, '1240439408', 'Mampong Waterfalls', '1240439408.jpg', 'After an hour''s drive from Accra to Mampong-Akwapim, this waterfalls is some 40 minutes walk from the Tetteh Quarshie Cocoa Farm, through the rocky forest of Mampong.The surroundings of Mampong falls provide visitors with wonderful peaceful scenery that refreshes the mind. ', NULL, 471, '2009-04-22 21:34:29', '2009-04-22 21:34:29', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 28, 7, 1, NULL),
