(655, '1240771777', 'Banku and Chicken soup', '1240771777.jpg', 'Banku is one of the many staple foods in Ghana. Although it is said to have originated from the Volta Region by the Ewes, it is enjoyed by different tribes in Ghana. Ingredients: Fermented corn/cassava dough mixed proportionally and cooked in hot water into a smooth whitish consistent paste. Served with soup, stew or a pepper sauce with fish. ', NULL, 794, '2009-04-26 18:43:53', '2009-04-26 18:43:53', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 4, 1, 1, NULL),
