(1911, '1263556389', 'Hohoe Post Office', '1263556389.jpg', 'That beauty contest, organized by the Department of Social\r\nWelfare, was held at the Accra Community Centre on March 4, 1957, and 22-year old Miss Amekoafia, from Alavanyo in the erstwhile Trans VoltaTogoland now Volta Region, represented the Greater Accra Region.\r\nMr John Peter Amewu, the Hohoe District Chief Executive, said the\r\nerection of the statuette was to immortalize the late Miss Ameakoafia\r\nas an instrument of inspiration to the present generation especially\r\nthe youth.Mamaga Dewotornyo I, Queen of Gbi Traditional Area,\r\ncommended the district assembly for honouring Miss Amekoafia.\r\n\r\n', NULL, 524, '2010-01-15 11:47:10', '2010-01-15 11:47:10', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 3, 1, 1, NULL),
(1912, '1263556803', 'Statuette of Miss Ghana 1957', '1263556803.jpg', 'The statuette of Miss Ghana 1957, Monica Amekoafia of blessed was unveiled at a brief ceremony as part of the country''s Golden Jubilee celebration at Hohoe. The statuette, erected in front of the Hohoe Post Office, was in ivory and christened "Miss Monica Amekoafia" or "Miss Ghana." The statuette depicts Miss Amekoafia as a gem of Ghanaian beauty wearing a crown with a sash across her right shoulder with an inscription Miss Ghana.\r\n', NULL, 1082, '2010-01-15 11:47:10', '2010-01-15 11:47:10', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 5, 1, 1, NULL),
