(2911, '5023989b2f63c', 'Fort Good Hope', '5023989b3025f.jpg', 'Fort Good Hope is situated in the little town of Senya Beraku in Ghana.In 1667 the Dutch established a lodge in Senya Beraku. In 1705-06, on invitation of the local Agona chief, they built a small stone triangular fort. They called it Fort de Goede Hoop, which translates to Fort Good Hope, for they hoped that trade in gold, ivory and slaves would boom. The fort was built on a promontory near a cove with a good landing beach.', NULL, 103, '2012-08-09 10:45:01', '2012-08-09 10:45:01', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, NULL),
